1. Bilateral cryptorchidism: This condition is characterized by the undescended testicles of newborn boys and can be associated with various other anomalies.
2. High palate: A high palate can be associated with various craniofacial syndromes.
3. Abnormal mandible morphology: Abnormal jaw development can be associated with genetic syndromes or skeletal dysplasias.

6. Premature rupture of membranes: This condition is characterized by the rupture of the amniotic sac before labor and can be associated with various causes, including genetic factors.
7. Poor suck: Poor suck can be associated with various neonatal conditions, including genetic disorders.
8. Lactic aciduria: This condition is characterized by high levels of lactic acid in the urine and can be associated with various metabolic disorders.
9. Poor appetite: Poor appetite can be associated with various conditions, including genetic syndromes.
10. Abnormality of the palmar creases: Abnormal palmar creases can be associated with various genetic syndromes.
